                        <p class="small text-muted">Edit <code>docker-compose.windows.yml</code> and update the volume paths:</p>
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-2 rounded small"><code># Find these lines in docker-compose.windows.yml
volumes:
  - C:\MCBDSManager\bedrock-server:/bedrock
  - C:\MCBDSManager\backups:/app/backups
  - C:\MCBDSManager\config:/app/config

# Change to your desired paths, for example:
volumes:
  - D:\Minecraft\bedrock-server:/bedrock
  - E:\Backups\minecraft:/app/backups
  - D:\Minecraft\config:/app/config</code></pre>

                        <p class="small mt-3"><strong>Example Configuration:</strong></p>
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-2 rounded small"><code># Using D: drive for game files and E: drive for backups
